answers.body_markdown:
Take a look at the JavaDoc of [`setAllowedFields`](https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/DataBinder.html#setAllowedFields-java.lang.String...-):

&gt; *&quot;Register fields that should be allowed for binding. Default is all fields. Restrict this for example to avoid unwanted modifications by
&gt; malicious users when binding HTTP request parameters.&quot;*

Which means that by default all fields are allowed. If you don&#39;t want to allow all fields, then you can specify the allowed fields in this method.

Similarly for the [`setDisallowedFields`](https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/DataBinder.html#setDisallowedFields-java.lang.String...-): 

&gt; *&quot;Register fields that should not be allowed for binding. Default is none. Mark fields as disallowed for example to avoid unwanted
&gt; modifications by malicious users when binding HTTP request
&gt; parameters.&quot;*

Which means that by default no field is disallowed. If you want to disallow some of the fields, then you can specify the disallowed fields in this method.

-----

So the answer to your question is that `setAllowedFields()` will automatically disallow the non-specified fields, but `setDisallowedFields()` will not automatically allow the non-specified fields (unless you didn&#39;t include them in `setAllowedFields()` too).

To support my answer, let me include the Spring&#39;s implementation of [`isAllowed`](https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/DataBinder.html#isAllowed-java.lang.String-): 

	protected boolean isAllowed(String field) {
		String[] allowed = getAllowedFields();
		String[] disallowed = getDisallowedFields();
		return ((ObjectUtils.isEmpty(allowed) || PatternMatchUtils.simpleMatch(allowed, field)) &amp;&amp;
				(ObjectUtils.isEmpty(disallowed) || !PatternMatchUtils.simpleMatch(disallowed, field)));
	}

You can clearly see that if a field is present in `allowedFields` and not present in `disallowedFields` only then it will be allowed. Otherwise, it won&#39;t be allowed.
